  volume    = {427},
  abstract  = {Observations of distant supernovae and the fluctuations in the cosmic
               microwave background (CMB) indicate that the expansion of the Universe
               may be accelerating under the action of a `cosmological constant' or
               some other form of `dark energy'. This dark energy now appears to
               dominate the Universe and not only alters its expansion rate, but also
               affects the evolution of fluctuations in the density of matter, slowing
               down the gravitational collapse of material (into, for example, clusters
